<div><h3>FIN 5401 - Investments </h3>  <p><hr>This course provides an introduction to investment theory and security valuation. In addition, students will gain a strong understanding of financial markets and the major classes of financial assets. The topics covered in the course include: ethics, equity and bond pricing, capital asset pricing model, behavioral finance, option pricing, and portfolio analysis. The lectures and examinations will focus both on quantitative and conceptual foundations.</p>

<p> </p>

<p> <br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> No prerequisites for MSF students. Prerequisite for other students is <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93154" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93154&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93154&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt4608" target="_blank">FIN 4200</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> and is by permission only.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered Annually<br><br></p><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt4608"></div></div>		</td>
